utterances.utterance: OK. Pencil neck aside, if Barack Obama, Kennedy, had used the words that Trump uses like that we just bleeped would you be offended?

utterances.speaker: KENNEDY
utterances.utterance: It's really hard to offend me. Absolutely -- but, you know, it is --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I did during the break.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Let's not bring that up again.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: OK.

utterances.speaker: KENNEDY
utterances.utterance: We're having a great time. God bless his soul. I miss you, dad. He knows, it's fine. So --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: The language? The nicknames? What do you think?

utterances.speaker: KENNEDY
utterances.utterance: I'm not a huge fan of this nickname. I thought on the grand scale of nicknames this one was a little bit mean.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Did you think he could have done better? Oh, it was mean.

utterances.speaker: KENNEDY
utterances.utterance: It was a little mean because there's nothing you can do about your neck like little Marco Rubio.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: There's nothing you can do about crooked either.

utterances.speaker: KENNEDY
utterances.utterance: Well.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: She's just plain crooked.

utterances.speaker: KENNEDY
utterances.utterance: Many choices about her crookedness. She could have made many choices in her past and not compromised herself completely as a human being, but she didn't make those choices.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: OK. So Kennedy not fully satisfied with pencil neck. Dana, what do you think? You're not a fan.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: I don't like the nicknames even though -- remember the only one I liked --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: I forget.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: -- little rocket man. That one I really liked. On the point of the Adam Schiff, nine Republicans on the House Intelligence Committee came together and all unanimously said he should step down as chairman. To me, that was significant because it wasn't like you had Devin Nunes on the committee saying, oh, he should have step down. Or if you had somebody like Jim Jordan or Mark Meadows who are on TV, or Matt Gaetz on TV defending the president all the time. You see people who were in the intelligence community actually worked for us in the intelligence community like Will Hurd, Elise Stefanik. It wasn't hard for them to get to the point of saying, yeah, he should step down. So substantively I thought like that spoke some voluminous --

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Can I quickly jump in and say nobody called for Devin Nunes to step down even though he engaged in much worse --

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: I'm sure they did.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: And Nunes got killed by the way, Juan. Killed by the Democrats and the media for doing nothing. And he was right the whole time.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: -- stooge for the White House. But nobody called --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Schiff was a stooge for Brennan.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: You missed my point. Nobody called for him to step down. Trey Gowdy, five years on Benghazi. Anybody say, hey, give it up? Step down?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: OK. Let me ask you, Greg.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Shoot.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: People like Swalwell and people like Schiff rode this collusion wave to the top. It raised their profile, they've raised a lot of money off of this, and now that it's kind of evaporated don't you think they deserve to get whacked?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: This is a great point because that wasn't a victory lap. It was a victory butt kicking. There's a great article in the Atlantic by either McKay Coppins, or McCoffins McKay, or McKay B. Coffins K.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: I love that one.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yes, it was about the collusion business model all these guys making money and building twitter followers and writing books. A guy name Seth Abramson. All these like charlatans. And so -- I think it's going to be interesting right now. I was at the gym -- not right now.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: You look great.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Thank you by the way. I almost got sick on the stair climber watching CNN. They're running out of stuff. They did -- they reported a poll that said that Trump is seen by the majority as ill tempered. That's what they were talking about for like 10 minutes. So they went from he's a spy to, you know, he's really mean.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Yep.

utterances.speaker: KENNEDY
utterances.utterance: Yeah. And Schiff did the same thing. Schiff downgraded from conspiracy and collusion to coordination, maybe communication. By the way, who got a special shout out from the president last night?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yes, Greg Jarret, I believe. You know what it is? They went from Kobe beef to like, you know, tofu dogs.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: You've really come around, Greg.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Oh, boy.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: All right --

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Oh, boy.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: -- giving us a preview of what's to come in the 2020 races, more from his explosive rally last night.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: I knew that. I knew that.

utterances.speaker: KENNEDY
utterances.utterance: Jesse got the name of the band wrong, just say no.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Gin Blossoms.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Gin Blossoms.

utterances.speaker: KENNEDY
utterances.utterance: All right. It is game on for -- is it close?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I don't think so.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: I don't think it's close.

utterances.speaker: KENNEDY
utterances.utterance: Game on for President Trump now that collusion is in his rearview mirror. In an explosive rally the president giving us a preview of what's to come this campaign season by taking aim at Democrats and their radical agenda, watch.

utterances.speaker: TRUMP
utterances.utterance: The Democrat Party has never been further outside of the mainstream. They are being brought so far left. Radical Democrats are the party of high taxes, open borders, late-term abortion, crime, hoaxes, and delusions.

utterances.speaker: KENNEDY
utterances.utterance: Oh, the president also mocking his opponent for pushing the Green New Deal.

utterances.speaker: TRUMP
utterances.utterance: I'd rather not talk about it tonight because I don't want to talk them out of it too soon because I love campaigning against the Green New Deal. I want them to make that a big part of their platform. No more airplanes, no more cows, one car per family.

utterances.speaker: KENNEDY
utterances.utterance: All right. He even had some fun at Democrats' expense on wind power.

utterances.speaker: TRUMP
utterances.utterance: If Hillary got in you'd be doing wind, wind mills, and if it doesn't -- if it doesn't blow, you can forget about television for that night. Darling, I want to watch television. I'm sorry, the wind isn't blowing.

utterances.speaker: TRUMP
utterances.utterance: I know a lot about wind.

utterances.speaker: KENNEDY
utterances.utterance: He does. Beautiful wind. So, Greg, it looks like you want to make some wind right now.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Ah, the strong wind will be coming your way shortly. He's like an arena rock band, right? And now he's got some new songs because we -- you know, build the wall used to be free bird. And lock her up was stairway to heaven. But now he's got the collusion delusion which sounds like a guns and roses album, by the way.

utterances.speaker: KENNEDY
utterances.utterance: Use your collusion one.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yeah. But not the Gin Blossoms. And Green New Deal is now kind of now replacing his lock her up. I also have to say -- I actually don't mind the swearing from before if you do it sparingly. And I think it's good to break that seal. We all swear. So why do we pretend like we don't swear. Also, I can't stop thinking about Adam Schiff's neck. So it works. Do you know what I mean? I never thought about his neck. Now I'm thinking about his neck. The one thing I missed from this rally he should have thanked Vlad, like in the middle. And you could hear -- you could hear Michael Moore's head explode. David Frum's head explode. Tom Arnold's head explode. And he -- just move on. I just like to thank Vlad and just move on.

utterances.speaker: KENNEDY
utterances.utterance: Doesn't Tom Arnold want to fight you.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I hope so. Either that or run away together.

utterances.speaker: KENNEDY
utterances.utterance: No judgement. So, Dana, the Green New Deal -- the president -- he's not even joking about that. He would love to run against that. And the fact that all of the Democrat senators who are running for president went on the record to endorse and support it, I think has been a gift to this president.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: And Hillary Clinton's daughter Chelsea Clinton sent a tweet to the president today saying, actually, that's not how wind power works, and here's a link to your own energy department explaining it to you. But I'm pretty sure the president is not going to care about that. Can I nerd out for just one second about this rally?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Just one second?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Something --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: How about eight years?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Something different about this rally than his rallies in 2016. Does anybody know what it is?

utterances.speaker: KENNEDY
utterances.utterance: He sweated more.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: In 2016 they did not have a mechanism on the Trump campaign to gather information on anybody who wanted to come in, right? So now what's different is that Brad Parscale at the Trump campaign has a system where if you want a ticket to the rally you've got to sign in, you've got to register. And what do you get from that? You have the ability then to contact them throughout the campaign whether small dollar donations, getting people to volunteer, put up a sign, maybe make sure your neighbor gets to the voting booth because they only won Michigan by 11,000 votes. And so, I think that something that -- looks like a hidden story of last night and kind of nerdy but really important, I think. Think how many people -- 25,000 people wanted to get in, they have all that information now.

utterances.speaker: KENNEDY
utterances.utterance: That's a great point. But that's a political application of something like -- say metrics in baseball.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Can I continue to nerd out with you?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Oh, geez.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Because I had Brad Parscale on my show and he told me exactly what he told you. And now that we have the numbers from Michigan, they said about 30 percent of these people at the rally were Democrats. And a massive amount of them were independents and a lot of them were also new voters who had never voted before. And so, they get their cell phones and then they can make those kinds of determinations and he actually said, they are harvesting a million new votes per week in each key swing state across the country. It's a phenomenal job that they're doing out there and they actually said, they're going to start expanding the maps of the Democrats aren't necessarily going to be playing defense in the Rust Belt. Brad was talking about having them play defense in states like Minnesota and New Mexico. So, I don't think the Democrats are even going to realize what hit them. And to be honest with you, they didn't even really deserve to win the midterms elections, because if you think about why Juan, they had the clout of the Russia hoax hanging over them. They had Republican members of the House retiring early. The base of the Democratic Party was all jacked up from impeachment because of the Russian hoax. If they had settled this thing before the midterms, it might have been a different outcome.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Well, to me again what struck me last night is, he spends a whole--

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: You're jealous.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Sorry?

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: You're jealous.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Jealous of what.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: Republicans have someone they really want to--

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Come on, it's like world wrestling or something. People just say, hey, the spectacle, it's in town, the circus is here. Let me go. That's why I say, for a victory lap, I was somewhat disappointed.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: Vince McMahon is worth $3.2 billion.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Fine. But I'm just telling you, people will be attracted to a spectacle. It doesn't mean that they're offering political support. We see polls now says like 56 percent of Americans say, I'm not voting for Trump. That's a big number. But let me just say--

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: Didn't they say that last night?

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: No. He says, I am building the wall. Last night, he went on a larger how he his building the wall, the press won't give him credit. And so, I'm thinking what is going on here. The reality is, there is no funding and he is not building a wall, but he tells people this like it's true. And then he says this in a way that distills his failure to keep his campaign promise. And it's not only on that. You know--

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Next week, he's going to Southern California to watch new all construction being built. We watched that on the show Juan, I want to apologize.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I just I want to talk to Juan's point about the people that come to see Donald Trump. This is a different kind of President. When you talk about President Obama, there was much passion for him from the media. They looked at him with reverence, not because they wanted to hug him but because they wanted to kneel before him.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: A Messiah.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: What you're seeing here is the exact opposite. You're actually seeing a human response to a human being. These are people that when they see Donald Trump, I know - they want to hug him because they tell me that, because they actually have a genuine affection for him. So, I wouldn't dismiss this as purely a spectacle. When you see those people there, they're not there because it's a circus. They're there because they like that guy.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: No. They're there because he pushes the fear button in particular, but says - uses profanities--

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Can't dismiss him like that Juan.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Obama was a bad uplift.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: Dana, updated to button this up with a nice bow.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Ok. So, I was just going to add one thing about these new people that they're finding to nerd out at the end. In El Paso, do you remember when the President went there about like three or four weeks ago and he had a big rally down there.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: Had and Beto had a big rally.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: I think it was saying like 30 percent of the people that came were Democrats. They are union members and they're Hispanic. And now I don't know if they mean they come to the rally and they all of a sudden become dedicated Trump followers, but they're curious enough to come and they've registered, so now they have the information and they're going to be able to talk to them--

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: And they're going to get more information--

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: And they will have appeals for donations.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: One last thing before we go.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: More just a moment.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: I was going to say.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: Here's Juan. Yay.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: All right. I won't say it.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: President Trump now threatening to shut down the southern border. He says, it will stop illegal immigration. The President, explaining why earlier.

utterances.speaker: DONALD TRUMP, PRESIDENT
utterances.utterance: We have the weakest, the most pathetic, the most laughed at immigration laws anywhere in the world. They're the Democrats laws. And I got stuck with them. We have two brand new caravans coming up if you can believe it, two big ones. We've run out of room. We have this ridiculous catch and release program where you catch him, and then you're supposed to release him. Mexico is going to have to do something otherwise I'm closing the border.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Wow. This is what I wanted to talk about Kennedy. So, he says he wants to shut down the southern border. Now, I don't think we're that kind of country. I think maybe after 9/11 we might shut it for a few hours, but we've never done something like this. And it would have tremendous impact on commerce. Remember there are huge trading partner in Mexico. It would have a huge impact--

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: Oil, strawberries.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Well, I don't know what else, but I think there is lots of commerce. And secondly, on workers and American industry again. So, what do you think?

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: I think that if the President does this by executive fiat that he will be challenged in the courts and he will probably not succeed, as President Obama didn't. And I think this also adds to the confusion which is why so many people are coming over the border and trying to get in, because they're convinced that the border is going to be sealed at some point. And he's absolutely right. Congress has not done their job and they have created so much more chaos and so many more uncertainties. And if you talk to individual members of Congress. Oh! Yes, well I really want to do something about it, but my colleagues they certainly don't, because they're lazy and they only work 12 days a year. But when the President is forceful and makes these declarations, it only makes more people come over worrying the door is going to shut for good.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: So, Jesse, we were discussing and going back and forth on the wall, no wall and his rant last night, but here remember he said he didn't have to do the wall, because he just thought if he declared a national emergency, he might do it more quickly, but he didn't have to do it. Now he's saying, I'm going to close the border. Does that strike you as a little bit much?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Well, we have a hot economy. People want to come here, and Mexico is doing absolutely nothing to stop all of these family units from Central America just coming right across their country up north. And you know because of the loopholes, people want to be here because they know they can get amnesty and their kids can get in. And you know they can live a much better life. But the Democrats are lying about the border just as they were lying about the Russia hoax. We now have Jeh Johnson, who is the DHS Secretary under Barack Obama saying, it's a crisis. You had today on CNN, the Chief of the Customs and Border Patrol Deputy who's Hispanic say, it's an absolute crisis. They don't have the capacity. They don't have the manpower or the infrastructure. They can't handle it. Right now, they're projecting over 100,000 illegal entries this month alone that is over a 10-year high. And if Congress doesn't do anything about it, the President has to act.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Well, that's a good point because I think our asylum laws are such that people say that if you can apply for asylum in the United States in terms of fleeing violence or even in terms of saying that you are politically oppressed that you have a right to be in the United States. And secondly, of course there are the laws that say that people coming from Central America as opposed to Mexico are to be treated differently, Dana. So, from what I'm hearing from both Kennedy and Jesse is, hey, America could solve this problem if we did something about our laws.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Absolutely. There's just no question. You could actually do a lot and it probably - they could probably work it out in a weekend, if they were willing to and everyone is going to have to understand, nobody is going to get everything that they want. That's what a compromise is going to be about. But I don't think the President is suggesting shutting down the border because he wants to. I think he very much does not want to. But I think that they're leaving him no choice, because the Homeland Security Secretary is pleading for help. She is saying, I cannot guarantee who is coming into this country. I need help. I don't know what else she can do to try to convince people that she has absolute has to have some help. Remember what happened with Angela Merkel saying, I'll take a million refugees here in Germany and then we all look at that and go wow that was - ultimately was a terrible decision. They had 100,000 try to cross in March. OK. So, you do 100,000--

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: We're on pace for over a million this year.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Overnight in one year. And what they're saying also is that we want to take care of them. We don't have enough beds to take care of the child.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: Poor judges.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Right.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: And Congresswoman Shalala today on the daily briefing said, well, they haven't even staffed up at the border enough. Right because they're in total crisis mode over there and you can't make good decisions when you are in a crisis. And maybe the way to have to get everybody to focus is the President might have to do something as drastic as shutting down the border. I don't think he wants to do it, but I think they're leaving him no choice.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: But Greg I think part of the problem is, it's become so highly politicized.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Right.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: And it's been politicized for a long time going back to George W. Bush who tried to do something, but now after Trump talks about an invasion, these people are gangsters, they're terrorists, they're rapist. People are like well jeez this is too political.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: He was talking about that within large groups of people there can be unsavory people within it. That's what he's talking about. Trump is - I think Trump is frustrated over that point. The stalemate is purely political. He blames both parties. That's what I think fueled his anger. And I think the Merkel decision is the thing that changed the framing for our country. Look you can't - Democrats liberals have to understand, you can't have a no fuss border and great government programs. You can't have them at the same time. Right. Because if you want an awesome safety net, you've got to seal the border. The whole country is going to crumble because everybody is going to want to be in the place where there is lots of free stuff.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: So, to that point.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Don't more people in fact I'm thinking here of terrorists come across the northern border. He's not talking about sealing the northern border.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Well, he's not a huge influx of Canadians Juan.

utterances.speaker: MONTGOMERY
utterances.utterance: What do Canadians do, if you go to Canada, if you go to some of the border towns, there are people from Mexico and Central America working so what do Canadians do with illegal immigrants who make it all the way through the United States?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: OK. The Dems are Jekyll in hiding this. It's a crisis, it's no crisis, it's a crisis, it's no crisis, only when it suits their needs. I'm with Kamala Harris who tweeted today that this is a humanitarian crisis.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Right. I would agree.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: OK. There we are.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: All right. We have agreement on. Fan Mail Friday, it's up next on THE FIVE.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I wouldn't say that's Tiki music. I would ask for Tiki music. All right, Fan Mail. First question from Carl Smith. What's the worst thing you've eaten out of politeness? Juan?

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Horse.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Horse. You eat horse.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: I didn't want to. It was out of polite.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Where.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Look at you, you're supposed to be my friend. You're laughing at my - because I ate a horse. This is too much.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: I was going to say, a crow. A single show.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Jesse?

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Serve cold brother. You're going to try some shortly.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Where did you eat horse?

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: I was in Japan and I was the guest of some fancy Korean people.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Wow.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: I had no choice.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Oh, my goodness. All right, Jesse.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: I had Ethiopian food with my hands like sitting Indian style on a mat, like that. And it was horrible. But I was polite.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Well, that's good. That's good. Dana, you probably--

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: I think lamb.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: You don't like lamb?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: No.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Too gamey.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: And it's usually rare.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Too cute. It's hard to eat cute animals.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Also, I hate horse, but I didn't know I was eating horse and they did it to see how I would react and then they told me later and I was furious.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: These are your friends?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: I'll never forget it Peter and David Hagel.

utterances.speaker: WILLIAMS
utterances.utterance: Oh! It was your husband.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: By the way, Greg Gutfeld thought veal was an animal.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yes, I did.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Like a veal was good. You didn't know.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yes. I told you that in the break a while ago.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
